message.en_US: Hello, seeker! Is there anything I can help with?
This is the \c[3]Summoners' Lobby\c[0]!
Anyone is welcome here, but only \i[class-star]\c[3]Starcaller\c[0] characters can actually summon allies.
Or characters from XPC that support Starcaller \c[3]custom skills\c[0].
The signs in this room can be used to equip different allies for each of your elements.
Your current ally capacity is \c[3]\v[plot.starcaller2.maxAllies]\c[0]. This will automatically increase each time you unlock new elements.
The ally you summon while in each element mode depends on what is equipped here.
[nods]
An \c[3]ally\c[0] is an enemy that you can summon to fight for you!
Allies have their own stats and abilities, but are always scaled to your current level.
You can only summon \c[3]\v[plot.starcaller2.maxAllies]\c[0] of them at a time with your current ally capacity.
The maximum capactiy is \c[3]5\c[0] once you unlock all the elements!
You can summon multiple of the same ally type, or you can spawn a variety since you will have a different summon equipped for each element.
Allies will slowly lose HP points automatically during combat. You can support them with your own combat arts that apply healing or buffs.
Each ally has its own summon cost in both of your own \c[3]HP\c[0] and \c[3]SP\c[0].
More powerful allies will be more expensive, so be sure to consider the risks and rewards!
It's possible to \c[1]defeat yourself\c[0] if you try to summon while your own \c[3]HP\c[0] is less than the summoning cost.
[nods]
To summon, you must first be a \i[class-star]\c[3]Starcaller\c[0] character. Double-tap the \c[3]guard\c[0] action to perform a summon.
The specific ally that you summon will depend on what your current element is, as well as what ally you have equipped for that element in this room.
It's not possible to equip two different ally types for the same element at once, so choose carefully!
[nods]
Hmm, let me see...\.. I have a note from Xenon about this...
"Right now, there are only a few ally options implemented in the mod. There are no unlock conditions or anything for now."
"Just go to the sign in this room and all currently implemented allies will be shown in the list".
"However, the eventual vision for the mod is to have different allies be unlocked automatically based on story and quest progress."
"For example, clearing the Rookie Harbor turret quests would unlock the \c[3]Rhombus Turret\c[0] ally."
"And clearing the Bergen Mines would unlock the \c[3]Digging Bot\c[0] ally."
"This would make it so some are optional based on quests, and others are automatic based on the main story progress."
"There would be a popup each time new ally options are unlocked. This would simply be patched into the existing cutscenes at the end."
...\! It looks like that's all that written on the note.
[nods]
Alright, look.
This isn't Xenon's main mod and he didn't put much effort into decorating this place.
If you want some more life in this room, as well as fixing the doorway outside and the minimap, perhaps we need to show that the Starcaller2 mod is more popular first.
Or perhaps \c[3]HeartLychee\c[0], the artist whom this mod was made for as thanks for helping with XPC, might be interested in decorating it personally.
The original plans were to have an elevator and different floors for each element.
Each floor would have a little exhibit platform to show off the potential allies in a passive state, along with details and attack demonstration buttons.
But that is a lot of work, and again this is not Xenon's main project.
So for now, you are stuck with this basic room and basic menu lists for choosing summon options.
[nods]
Bye!
